<div class="entry">
  <div class="entry-title">Design of a Toyota 5-Speed Manual Transmission for FWD Cars</div>
  <div class="entry-meta">Mechanical Design · December 2020</div>
  <p>
    Full design of a Toyota 5-speed manual transmission gearbox covering <strong>gears</strong>,
    <strong>shafts</strong>, <strong>bearings</strong>, <strong>housing</strong>, and
    <strong>mechanical keys</strong>. Gear design in mechanical engineering is a complex process —
    power is transmitted through speed and torque via meshing gear teeth, and every component
    in the drivetrain has to be sized, analysed, and validated.
  </p>

  <figure style="text-align:center; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
    <img src="https://i.ibb.co/ZXCtnjq/Assembly1.png" alt="Gearbox assembly in Autodesk Inventor" style="max-width:560px; width:100%;">
  </figure>

  <p>Design began from the known gear ratios:</p>

