  <h3>Gears</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Number of teeth per gear calculated based on the minimum tooth count per gear</li>
    <li>Rotational speed and torque derived for each stage</li>
    <li>Diametral pitch selected based on gearbox size constraints; diameter and centre distance calculated</li>
    <li>AGMA bending and contact stress analysis performed for all gear pairs</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Shafts</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Shaft length determined by gear face widths, bearing widths, and collar spacing — resulting in 38 in</li>
    <li>Initial material CD 1020 with FoS 1.25 required a 1.08 in diameter; switched to AISI 1060,
      which brought the diameter under 1 in — rounded up to 1 in, with recalculated safety factors
      meeting company requirements</li>
    <li>Maximum deflection calculated at <strong>0.02227 in</strong> using a 200 GPa modulus of
      elasticity and 0.7853 in⁴ second moment of area</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Bearings</h3>
  <p>
    With reaction forces and bore diameters known, ball bearings were selected from standard tables
    and verified against inventory for suitability.
  </p>

  <h3>Mechanical Keys</h3>
  <p>
    Key selection based on shaft sizing. Square keys chosen — fatigue failure is less critical
    under distortion energy theory and equivalent to the maximum shear stress theory.
  </p>

